description.narrative: 1. Hazardous and Suspected Hazardous Areas assigned are released in accordance with National Standards to the benefit of the affected community. 2. Awareness of risks of landmines and Explosive Remnants of War-related accidents for women, men, girls and boys in contaminated areas is increased through Risk Education. 3. Victims of landmines and Explosive Remnants of War-related accidents and their families are supported through access to basic life support and first aid response, and psycho-social support in affected areas. 4. Accountability and technical capacities of South Sudan partners are reinforced.
"Enhanced resiliance of vulnerable groups through Improved access to resources, livelhoods and socioeconomic reconstruction"
